# reversi

An implementation of the strategic board game Reversi, written in Clojure, with
three different user interfaces.

(See: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reversi for details on rules, strategy, etc.)

## Usage

At the promp, create a standalone JAR using lein:

$ lein uberjar

This will generate a jar such as clojure-reversi-0.1.0-SNAPSHOT-standalone.jar

To run the text version of the game:

$ java -jar clojure-reversi-0.1.0-SNAPSHOT-standalone.jar text

To run the Quil version of the game:

$ java -jar clojure-reversi-0.1.0-SNAPSHOT-standalone.jar quil

To run the Swing version of the game:

$ java -jar clojure-reversi-0.1.0-SNAPSHOT-standalone.jar swing

